## Game Design Non-Negotiables

| Rule | Rationale |
|------|-----------|
| No instant max-level gratification | Destroys long-term engagement |
| No purchasable power via real money | Pay-to-win destroys community |
| Breakthrough must have failure risk | Without risk, advancement is hollow |
| Alchemy must have quality variance | Quality is the skill ceiling |
| Economy must have sinks | Inflation destroys game health |
| No unbounded farming | Rate limits on all grindable actions |

---

## Testing Philosophy

- **Unit tests for core engine** — all formulas must be proven correct.
- **Integration tests for API services** — state changes must be verified.
- **No test = not done.** For any feature in `packages/core`.
- **Human verification for lore** — AI-generated narrative needs a human review pass.

